                            <comment id="194114" author="pjones" created="Tue, 2 May 2017 04:11:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IIUC this is fixed by the landing of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9359&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_27p: /mnt/lustre/d27p.sanity/f27p.sanity has size 4, not 80000004&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9359&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9359&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="193167" author="bobijam" created="Mon, 24 Apr 2017 04:11:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/26706/4&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/26706/4&lt;/a&gt;&#160;contains the fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch fixes the misunderstanding of ost_pool::op-&amp;gt;size, it indicates the buffer size allocated instead of the array count. Another issue fixed is that in lod_alloc_qos(), only fill in the ost inused array when the lod_qos_declare_object_on() succeeds.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
